Martin,

Ya did good!  

Every minor detail can add up when sealing and heat proofing an aircooled 
engine.

It is the ONE thing that almost all newbies and some old timers will 
ignore when trying to get the temperatures down.

I'm betting that your results are pretty much permanent...feels good 
doesn't it!

Cheers, dave

